cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.CL 

The paper presents a novel non-parametric clustering technique that is based on an iterative algorithm. The technique is evaluated on high-dimensional datasets that vary in size and characteristics, including deep features trained by a convolutional neural network. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of K-nearest neighbors and density-based clustering, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
